postcontent: Ok guys, so here’s the scoop. I’ve never listed a non firearm related item on here before and I’m sure many will recongnize my number because I list guns almost daily on here. Anyway, I work a tow business and I have acquired some extra vehicles that I’m not in need of and figured what could be better then turning them into some firearms to add to my collection. I have a 1995 Chevy S-10. It has a 2.2L 4-cylinder and a 5 speed transmission. It is all around a dam good little truck. It has some slight rust and a dent in the fender. The interior is a little dirty but in excellent condition. AC and everything on the truck works properly. It has a CD player with an amp and subwoofer behind the seat. The previous owner just spent a lot of money last month having a brand new Cylinder Head, Valves, Cam, and Timing chain installed as well as new brake lines. When you pop the hood you can look at the engine and automatically tell that everything up top is brand spanking new. The clutch went out so he kept trying to drive it and junked the transmission and that’s when I purchased it from him. I pulled a tranny out of a totaled 94 S-10 that only had 80k miles and installed a brand new clutch, pressure plate, throw out bearing when I put the new tranny in. The truck itself has 140k miles on it and anyone that knows these little trucks know they will push 250k-300k miles with ease as long as they are maintained. It will make someone a dam nice little gas saver to drive back and fourth. I’m looking to get $1,000 trade value out of it. I like anything from Glocks to 1911’s, AR’s, AR Pistols, AK’s. If it’s something you would be interested in checking out just shoot me a text at 812-374-4908 and I can give you further details and more pictures. My name is Charles by the way. Also the truck does have a single line crack across the windshield and very good matching tires all the way around. I think that’s about everything I can think of off the top of my head. Oh and YES it does have a CLEAN AND CLEAR TITLE ready to be signed. Thanks.
